New Records: Travis Head scored the highest individual score by an Australian in England, surpassing his previous best of 152.
Key Match Events: Travis Head scored an unbeaten 154 not out
Ben Duckett hit 95 in England's 315 all out
Australia's spinners took nine wickets, including 3-39 by Marnus Labuschagne
Post-Match Reflections: Travis Head expressed enjoyment in his batting and working hard over a few years
Harry Brook acknowledged difficulty against spinners and a below-par score
Miscellaneous Highlights: Will Jacks hit 62 for his third half-century in eight ODIs
Adam Zampa had 3-49 off 10 overs in his 100th ODI
Australia's lead spinner Adam Zampa had 3-49 off 10 overs in his 100th ODI
Ben Dwarshuis sustained a suspected pectoral strain and did not return to the field
